comments.body:
Thanks for the feedback everyone! Glad you enjoyed our game!

I see a lot of comments about aiming of the torpedoes. I do agree that aiming without the upgrade is clunky and hard. Maybe the "homing effect" shouldn't be on/off like it is now, but rather the torpedoes should always home in on the mouse cursor and the effectiveness of the homing could be upgraded. :thinking: 

@fabula-rasa the aiming mechanic is by design. You make an excellent point! I added a note about the mouse aiming to the key bindings.

@drgrognak never played Operation Neptune. I can definitely see the similarities, though! :grinning:

Thanks everyone for playing the game!

@MatchaMaze
I agree the item interaction needs a bit work. We actually ran into that bug too ðŸ˜‚. Hope it didn't get you killed!

@Talia
Thanks that's very kind! You really got lucky in the boots department ðŸ˜.

@pikachurian
Shooting speed depends on your wand. Though I agree the first wands you get are a little too slow!

@TomBuston
The game could definitely use some balancing. Your suggestions sound like good ideas ðŸ‘!

@Juutis

> Did you check if the standalone build runs any smoother?

No, booting to Windows was too much of a hassle :)

Hi everyone and thanks for the feeback!

Hey @Kleinzach! Are you sure the glass blocks were bugged? To break a glass block you require quite a height to fall from.

@dwemthy I'm aware of the buggy platforming and I would like to fix it. This was my first attempt at a platformer so the implementation is very shoddy. If I work more on this that will be the first problem I'll tackle.

Hi @pvsevrain! Yeah, I really took the time to make levels. I implemented [TiledSharp](https://github.com/marshallward/TiledSharp) to use [Tiled Map Editor](https://www.mapeditor.org/) from the get-go, so making levels was simple and fast!

@Ztuu How many secret levels did you find? ;)

Thanks for playing my game guys!

@Wan it was cool that you noticed the &quot;shoot right after teleport&quot;-mechanic. I wanted that to be the main thing in the game but I didn't have enough time to make it satisfying enough, or to make levels that would teach it to the player.

Also, the the game  should have started off with levels without the teleporting projectile. The player could have moved by walking around and getting pulled in by some objects, perhaps hitting some switches... Let's say I would have liked to spend much more time on this than I did.
